# Cloudflare Pages routing for the SPA (built with base /mos/).
# The build output is FLAT (dist/index.html, dist/assets/*), but the app references
# its assets at /mos/assets/* (the base). On CF Pages those /mos/ paths have no real
# file, so we rewrite them onto the flat output. Existing files are served first;
# these rules only fire for the missing /mos/ paths. Order matters — assets before
# the SPA catch-all, or the catch-all would return index.html (text/html) for a .js
# request and the app renders blank.
/mos/assets/*  /assets/:splat  200
/mos/*         /index.html     200
